Package: OmniVerse
Title: Multi-Omics RNA Analysis Shiny Application
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Safa", "Rafique", email = "safa.res.sbb@pu.edu.pk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Shiny application for high-throughput genomic analysis of bulk RNA-seq and
  microarray data (e.g. from GEO). Integrates with Bioconductor (GEOquery, Biobase,
  limma, DESeq2, edgeR, clusterProfiler) for a single workflow: download, QC,
  normalization, batch correction, differential expression, WGCNA, pathway enrichment,
  PPI, machine learning, and optional immune deconvolution. Uses common data structures
  (ExpressionSet, DGEList) for interoperability. Install with BiocManager::install("OmniVerse").
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.5.0)
